  },
  {
    "@id": "https://saskatoonsymphony.org/temporary/69f1efa7-1654-4e0f-963f-8a2c752929ab",
    "@type": [
      "https://schema.org/CreativeWork"
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#wasDerivedFrom": [
      {
        "@id": "https://saskatoonsymphony.org/event/summer-sounds-2/"
      }
    ],
    "https://schema.org/text": [
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "\n\t\t\t\n\n\n7:00PM, Wednesday, July 29, 2026\nBlack Fox Farm & Distillery\n\n\nComp 117 Site, 245 Valley Road, 319 RR3\nSaskatoon, SK S7K 3J6\nGoogle Maps Directions\n\n\nSOLD OUT\n\n\n\nTHIS EVENT HAS REACHED MAXIMUM CAPACITY\nJoin us on Wednesday, July 29, as the Saskatoon Symphony Orchestra performs Hollywood favourites.\nFrom beloved movie themes to unforgettable cinematic scores, this year’s performance celebrates the music that has brought some of Hollywood’s most iconic stories to life.\nRoll out your blanket, gather your favourite co-stars, and join us for a cinematic evening under the prairie sky. Best of all, admission is free with advance RSVP.\nGuests are welcome to come early — bring a picnic, pick flowers in the field, and soak up the summer sun before the show. Arriving early also helps ease traffic congestion, so we’d love to see you before the orchestra takes the stage.\nEvent Details\nDate: Wednesday, July 29\n6:00 PM: DJ kicks off the evening\n7:00 PM: Saskatoon Symphony Orchestra performance\n8:00 PM: DJ returns to close out the night\nLocation: Black Fox Farm & Distillery\nUpgrade to VIP\nWant to elevate your evening? Our VIP experience includes:\n\nA complimentary cocktail\nAn individual charcuterie offering\nAccess to a dedicated VIP gathering area and bar\nReserved VIP parking upon arrival\nReserve Your Spot\n\nAttendance is limited and advance RSVP is required.\nHere is everything you need to plan your perfect evening at Summer Sounds:\n\n𝗔𝗿𝗿𝗶𝘃𝗮𝗹 𝗧𝗶𝗺𝗶𝗻𝗴: We’re anticipating heavy traffic into the farm, so please plan ahead and allow extra time for your arrival to ensure you don’t miss a moment of this special evening.\n𝗦𝗲𝗮𝘁𝗶𝗻𝗴 & 𝗖𝗼𝗺𝗳𝗼𝗿𝘁: Our natural amphitheater features primarily hillside seating, so we encourage bringing a cozy blanket for the most comfortable experience! If you prefer a flat surface, arrive early to secure one of the limited level spots.\n𝗗𝗶𝗻𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝗯𝘆 𝗦𝘂𝗻𝘀𝗲𝘁: We invite you to pack a picnic to enjoy during the performance! Our food offerings will be limited to delicious snacks.\n𝗙𝘂𝗿𝗿𝘆 𝗙𝗿𝗶𝗲𝗻𝗱𝘀: While we love all creatures, Black Fox is not a pet-friendly venue. Please leave your beloved companions at home for everyone’s safety and comfort.\n𝗣𝗿𝗮𝗶𝗿𝗶𝗲 𝗣𝗿𝗲𝗽: Don’t forget bug spray! Our beautiful natural setting means mosquitos may be joining the audience too.\n\nWhether you’re a lifelong movie lover, a symphony enthusiast, or simply looking for a memorable summer evening, we invite you to spread out a blanket, and experience the magic of Hollywood classics under the prairie sky.\nSummer Sounds at Black Fox, powered by ATB Wealth.\n\nAt ATB Wealth, our expert advice is tailored exclusively to your specific needs, so your priorities are our priorities. We are thrilled to offer our services with a local team in Saskatoon, offering proactive financial insight that adapts and innovates in an ever-changing world for you, your family, or your business.\nVisit http://www.atb.com/WealthSaskatoon for more information.\nATB Wealth® (a registered trade name) consists of a range of financial services provided by ATB Financial and certain of its subsidiaries. ATB Investment Management Inc. and ATB Securities Inc. are individually licensed users of ATB Wealth. ATB Securities Inc. is a member of the Canadian Investor Protection Fund and the Canadian Investment Regulatory Organization.\n\n\n\t\t"
      }
    ]
  },
