      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "@id": "https://saskatoonsymphony.org/temporary/1cb84ede-aa5c-470a-885c-2c3f7a036191",
    "@type": [
      "https://schema.org/WPHeader"
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#wasDerivedFrom": [
      {
        "@id": "https://saskatoonsymphony.org/event/the-elements/"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "@id": "https://saskatoonsymphony.org/temporary/9c4248c3-b234-46a3-a2d7-ae084d1bc228",
    "@type": [
      "https://schema.org/CreativeWork"
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#wasDerivedFrom": [
      {
        "@id": "https://saskatoonsymphony.org/event/the-elements/"
      }
    ],
    "https://schema.org/text": [
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "\n\t\t\t\n\n\n7:30PM, Saturday, September 12, 2026\nSt John’s Cathedral\n\n\n 816 Spadina Crescent E\nSaskatoon, Saskatchewan S7K 3H4\nGoogle Maps Directions\n\n\nSave Your Seats\n\n\n\nAlexa Haynes-Pilonconductor/cello\n\n\nLes ÉlémensJean-Frey Rebel\nSelections from both Handel’s and Telemann’s Water Music\nConcertos by Caldara, Durante, and Vivaldi\n\n\nAlexa Haynes-Pilon returns home to Saskatoon with a new baroque concert experience that she has designed just for this occasion. Baroque composers were captivated by the four elements—water, fire, air, and earth—and they found great curiosity in depicting the elements through musical imagery, using specific instrumentation and textures to evoke natural forces.\nAlexa will lead and solo with the SSO in the music of Jean-Frey Rebel’s Les Élémens, selections from both Handel’s and Telemann’s Water Music, and concertos by Caldara, Durante, and Vivaldi.\nWhile her career takes her around the globe performing and curating as a baroque specialist, Alexa’s roots in Saskatoon continue to call her home. Her 2023 debut with the SSO was a sold-out sensational performance that instantly meant we needed to bring her back again!\nIf you’re thinking about attending multiple shows, bundle your tickets and save!\n\n\n\t\t"
      }
    ]
  },
