  {
    "@id": "https://saskatoonsymphony.org/temporary/150237ce-112f-4257-93bc-b694559e6b41",
    "@type": [
      "https://schema.org/CreativeWork"
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#wasDerivedFrom": [
      {
        "@id": "https://saskatoonsymphony.org/event/hunchback-of-notre-dame/"
      }
    ],
    "https://schema.org/text": [
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "\n\t\t\t\n\n\n7:30PM, Thursday, October 1, 2026\nThe Roxy Theatre\n\n\n320 20th Street West\nSaskatoon, SK S7M 0X2\nGoogle Maps Directions\n\n\nSave Your Seats\n\n\n\nMichael Bridgedigital accordion\n\n\nAfter his sensational performance in 2024, where he improvised a full score for the silent film Phantom of the Opera, it was obvious that the audience needed more of Michael Bridge.\nNow returning to the historic Roxy Theatre, Bridge creates a new improvised score for the legendary silent film The Hunchback of Notre Dame. \nThe first film adaptation of Victor Hugo’s classic became an instant success and has remained one of the great silent feature films ever produced. \nMichael Bridge is a world-renowned digital accordionist who spins magic in these silent film experiences. \nBe immersed in Saskatoon’s very own historic Roxy Theatre and be transported back to the days of the silver screen…silence is golden!\nIf you’re thinking about attending multiple shows, bundle your tickets and save!\n\n\n\t\t"
      }
    ]
  },
