    ],
    "https://schema.org/text": [
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "\n\t\t\t\n\n\n7:00PM, Sunday, October 18, 2026\nBacchus Lounge – Earls\n\n\n610 2nd Ave N\nSaskatoon, SK S7K 2C7\nGoogle Maps Directions\n\n\nFill Out The Contact Form\n\n\n7:00PM, Monday, October 19, 2026\nBacchus Lounge – Earls\n\n\n610 2nd Ave N\nSaskatoon, SK S7K 2C7\nGoogle Maps Directions\n\n\nFill Out The Contact Form\n\n\n\nJulie NesrallahCarmen\n\n\nCarmen on Tap is a hip and immersive opera experience that brings the power and virtuosity of the human voice to you in an intimate setting at The Bacchus Lounge at Earls as you savour an incredible meal & stellar cocktails. \nWe’re transforming Bacchus Lounge into the scene of an intimate passionate experience, with the action taking place all around you. This is all thanks to the creative genius of Canada’s Carmen, Julie Nesrallah. \nNesrallah leads a stellar cast in an abridged performance of Bizet’s Carmen that places the audience at the centre of the drama. While hearing some of the greatest music ever written, you may find yourself being the centre of Carmen’s flirtatious affection, or swept off your feet by the Torreador himself!\nBe seduced.\nPrends garde a toi!\nContact the SSO office to save your seats. You can call the office at 306-665-6414 or fill out the contact form and we will get back to you.\n\n\n\t\t"
      }
    ]
  },
