  {
    "@id": "https://saskatoonsymphony.org/temporary/c6756e85-69be-44f7-9dcb-dd6cdfa27b66",
    "@type": [
      "https://schema.org/CreativeWork"
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#wasDerivedFrom": [
      {
        "@id": "https://saskatoonsymphony.org/event/handels-messiah-4/"
      }
    ],
    "https://schema.org/text": [
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "\n\t\t\t\n\n\n7:30PM, Friday, December 11, 2026\nKnox United Church\n\n\n838 Spadina Crescent E\nSaskatoon, SK S7K 3H4\nGoogle Maps Directions\n\n\nSave Your Seats\n\n\n\nKarl Hirzerconductor\nCasey Pedensoprano\nOli Gusellealto\nSpencer McKnighttenor\nNicholas Borgbass\nSSO ChorusDuff Warkentin & Kerry Agnew\n\n\nMessiahGeorge Frideric Handel\n\n\nPodium Partner Karl Hirzer returns to the intricate music of Handel for a third year in a row. If you had a chance to see the SSO and Chorus led by Hirzer in previous seasons, you know we’re in for a special treat. \nWe’re joined by soloists Casey Peden, Oli Guselle, Spencer McKnight, and Nicholas Borg, and the SSO Chorus led by Kerry Agnew and Duff Warkentin.\nIf you’re thinking about attending multiple shows, bundle your tickets and save!\n\n\n\t\t"
      }
    ]
  },
