        "@value": "Roman Holiday"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/description": [
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "Podium partner Karl Hirzer leads the SSO in a musical journey to Italy featuring Saskatoon’s own Ryan Davis returning home to join the SSO for Hector Berlioz’ adventurous Harold in Italy."
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/eventStatus": [
      {
        "@id": "http://schema.org/EventScheduled"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "@id": "https://saskatoonsymphony.org/temporary/6b5f9f22-1d66-453b-b8ba-07d445863137",
    "@type": [
      "https://schema.org/Blog"
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#wasDerivedFrom": [
      {
        "@id": "https://saskatoonsymphony.org/event/roman-holiday/"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "@id": "https://saskatoonsymphony.org/temporary/0b84e465-8b58-4f4d-821b-cb9d94c4063a",
    "@type": [
      "https://schema.org/WPHeader"
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#wasDerivedFrom": [
      {
        "@id": "https://saskatoonsymphony.org/event/roman-holiday/"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "@id": "https://saskatoonsymphony.org/temporary/ffe438ed-1eae-41e9-b31f-4f775b2fa89b",
    "@type": [
      "https://schema.org/CreativeWork"
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#wasDerivedFrom": [
      {
        "@id": "https://saskatoonsymphony.org/event/roman-holiday/"
      }
    ],
    "https://schema.org/text": [
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "\n\t\t\t\n\n\n7:30PM, Saturday, March 6, 2027\nTCU Place, Sid Buckwold Theatre\n\n\n35 – 22nd Street East\nSaskatoon, SK S7K 0C8\nGoogle Maps Directions\n\n\nSave Your Seats\n\n\n\nKarl Hirzerconductor\nRyan Davisviola\n\n\nHarold in Italy, Op. 16Hector Berlioz\nPines of RomeOttorino Respighi\n\n\nShake off those winter blues and take a much-needed trip to Rome!\nPodium partner Karl Hirzer leads the SSO in a musical journey to Italy featuring Saskatoon’s own Ryan Davis returning home to join the SSO for Hector Berlioz’ adventurous Harold in Italy.  \nAfter finding ourselves squarely in the musical language of Italy, the SSO walks with you through the Eternal City with Ottorino Respighi’s Pines of Rome. A musical photograph of areas of Rome that find themselves in the shades of trees, this work is amongst the most incredible and exhilarating ever written for orchestra.\nThis is a landmark night at the SSO, and one that will be remembered for years to come.\nCiao bella!\nIf you’re thinking about attending multiple shows, bundle your tickets and save!\n\n\n\t\t"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "@id": "https://saskatoonsymphony.org/event/verve/",
