    "http://schema.org/url": [
      {
        "@id": "https://saskatoonsymphony.org/event/how-to-train-your-dragon/"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/name": [
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "How To Train Your Dragon"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/description": [
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "When a young Viking defies tradition and befriends a ferocious dragon, together they must fight against all odds to save both their worlds. Experience this captivating film in HD, with its thrilling musical score performed live to picture!"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/eventStatus": [
      {
        "@id": "http://schema.org/EventScheduled"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "@id": "https://saskatoonsymphony.org/temporary/6ca0d7d5-c6d0-4b0d-9f54-3d029f9cbf02",
    "@type": [
      "https://schema.org/Blog"
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#wasDerivedFrom": [
      {
        "@id": "https://saskatoonsymphony.org/event/how-to-train-your-dragon/"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "@id": "https://saskatoonsymphony.org/temporary/8aad4305-9a01-441d-8dfc-5b6edf44cedc",
    "@type": [
      "https://schema.org/WPHeader"
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#wasDerivedFrom": [
      {
        "@id": "https://saskatoonsymphony.org/event/how-to-train-your-dragon/"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "@id": "https://saskatoonsymphony.org/temporary/ec5e939e-0e01-411e-9d57-bf25c215857b",
    "@type": [
      "https://schema.org/CreativeWork"
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#wasDerivedFrom": [
      {
        "@id": "https://saskatoonsymphony.org/event/how-to-train-your-dragon/"
      }
    ],
    "https://schema.org/text": [
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "\n\t\t\t\n\n\n7:30PM, Saturday, April 10, 2027\nTCU Place, Sid Buckwold Theatre\n\n\n35 – 22nd Street East\nSaskatoon, SK S7K 0C8\nGoogle Maps Directions\n\n\nSave Your Seats\n\n\n\nJuliane Gallantconductor\n\n\nA winner with audiences and critics alike, DreamWorks’ How to Train Your Dragon is a captivating and original story that combines humor, fire-breathing action and epic adventure! \nHiccup is a young Viking who defies tradition when he befriends one of his deadliest foes – a ferocious dragon he calls Toothless. Together, these unlikely heroes must fight against all odds to save both their worlds.\nHow To Train Your Dragon – In Concert features this acclaimed film presented in HD, with composer John Powell’s Academy Award®-nominated score performed live to picture by a full symphony orchestra in a thrilling experience for all ages.\nIf you’re thinking about attending multiple shows, bundle your tickets and save!\n\n\n\t\t"
      }
    ]
  },
