  {
    "@id": "https://saskatoonsymphony.org/temporary/f0fdb29e-3ba3-4a00-90bf-d7557160e57b",
    "@type": [
      "https://schema.org/CreativeWork"
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#wasDerivedFrom": [
      {
        "@id": "https://saskatoonsymphony.org/event/vers-la-flamme/"
      }
    ],
    "https://schema.org/text": [
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "\n\t\t\t\n\n\n7:30PM, Saturday, May 1, 2027\nTCU Place, Sid Buckwold Theatre\n\n\n35 – 22nd Street East\nSaskatoon, SK S7K 0C8\nGoogle Maps Directions\n\n\nSave Your Seats\n\n\n\nJudith Yanconductor\nNikki Chooiviolin\n\n\nAtashIman Habibi\n\n\nA concert designed specifically to connect directly with its audience, and through connection, move us forward. \nPodium Partner Judith Yan curates a unique concert experience as we move towards the flame. The evening features 5 brand new works by female composers (including Adriana Isabel Figueroa Manas and Kendra Harder) in a commissioning project entitled A Better World, supported by a generous donation from Carol Edwards. These works are interspersed throughout an evening of music where musical fire creates a new and better world. \nViolinist Nikki Chooi returns to the SSO after his 2015 debut in a brand new work co-commissioned by the SSO. Iman Habibi’s Atash was created in response to the devastating fires of 2023, and Habibi’s goal is to show our changing relationship with this powerful natural force, where the orchestra represents nature, and the soloist reacts to it as humans have done throughout history.\nOur earth, our society, each of us, finding a better world. Creating something from the ashes as we move towards the flame.\nIf you’re thinking about attending multiple shows, bundle your tickets and save!\n\n\n\t\t"
      }
    ]
  },
